.START 

Weyerhaeuser Co. 's board approved construction of a third newsprint machine and de-inking facility at the company's North Pacific Paper Corp. plant in Longview, Wash.
Weyerhaeuser said the project will cost more than $300 million, and will add more than 700,000 tons of yearly newsprint capacity. 

Weyerhaeuser added that Jujo Paper Co. of Japan will increase its equity interest in North Pacific Paper to 20% from 10%.
The Japanese market consumes about half of the mill's production. 

